data.name: buyCountIntegerInput.SuperTooltip
data.value: The size of the item stack when sold by vendors. Also if a vendor has limited copies of this item available, everytime the vendor list is refreshed (See npc_vendor.incrtime), the number of copies increases by this number.

data.name: itemWeaponStatsInfoLabel.Text
data.value:
Sheath: How the weapon is put away. Two-handed puts it on the back, crossed if the weapon is actually single handed. One handed puts it on the waist, etc.
Ammo Type: The kind of ammo it uses. Leave at No Ammo if it isnt a ranged weapon.
Delay: Weapon speed. Input is in milliseconds. Example: 3000 milliseconds = 3.0 seconds.
Block: How much block will be added when the item is equipped.
Armor: How much armor will be added once the item is equipped. Can be a negative amount.

data.name: itemReqInfoLabel.Text
data.value:
Required Level: What level the player (1-255) must be to use the item. Leave at blank for no requirement.
Item Level: Used to indicate the quality of the item numerically, also impacts enchanting requirements.
Reputation: Use this to set a required faction/reputation.
Rep. Rank: Set the level of Req Reputation you want.
Skill/Profession: Use this to set a required skill/profession.
Skill Level: Set the level of Req Skill you want.

data.name: itemResistsInfoLabel.Text
data.value:
Holy: How much holy resist will be added once the item is equipped. Leave blank for none. Can be a negative amount.
Fire: How much fire resist will be added once the item is equipped. Leave blank for none. Can be a negative amount.
Nature: How much nature resist will be added once the item is equipped. Leave blank for none. Can be a negative amount.
Frost: How much frost resist will be added once the item is equipped. Leave blank for none. Can be a negative amount.
Shadow: How much shadow resist will be added once the item is equipped. Leave blank for none. Can be a negative amount.
Arcane: How much arcane resist will be added once the item is equipped. Leave blank for none. Can be a negative amount.

data.name: itemSocketInfoLabel.Text
data.value:
Socket: Select what color socket you want on your item.
Socket Bonus: This bonus will become active when certain criteria are met - usually when all sockets are filled with gems that match the colors of the sockets.

data.name: flagsCustomIntegerInput.SuperTooltip
data.value:
1 - ITEM_FLAGS_CU_DURATION_REAL_TIME Item duration will tick even if player is offline
2 - ITEM_FLAGS_CU_IGNORE_QUEST_STATUS No quest status will be checked when this item drops
4 - ITEM_FLAGS_CU_FOLLOW_LOOT_RULES Item will always follow group/master/need before greed looting rules

data.name: foodTypeComboBox.SuperTooltip
data.value: If this item is a food type item, this field defines what type of food it is for hunters who want to feed their pets. It controls in what diet this food item falls in. NOTE: Raw meat and fish is not the same as regular meat and fish. It seems that the last two types of diets include grey "poor" types of food that players have no use for but some pets seem to be able to eat. Also, those food types appeared in TBC so most likely only TBC pets will have those types of diets.

data.name: randomSuffixIntegerInput.SuperTooltip
data.value: The number in this field points to item_enchantment_template.entry and ties in an item's chance at having a random suffix attached to it when it shows up for the first time. This field and the RandomProperty field CANNOT both have non-zero values. Either one is filled, or the other. Also, the primary source for the number in this field are WDBs.

data.name: randomPropIntegerInput.SuperTooltip
data.value: The number in this field points to item_enchantment_template.entry and ties in an item's chance at having a random property attached to it when it shows up for the first time. This field and the RandomSuffix field CANNOT both have non-zero values. Either one is filled, or the other. Also, the primary source for the number in this field are WDBs.

data.name: pageTextIntegerInput.SuperTooltip
data.value: The ID referring to the text that the item will show (if it is a book or a letter, etc). The item will have a magnifying glass cursor in the game and will show the text when right-clicked. See page_text.entry
